article.description: Dexter Werner scored 14 points with 10 rebounds to help North Dakota State top Western Illinois 65-52 on Saturday.
article.headline: Werner helps North Dakota State over Western Illinois 65-52
article.linkText: Werner helps North Dakota State over Western Illinois 65-52
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. -- Dexter Werner scored 14 points with 10 rebounds to help North Dakota State top Western Illinois 65-52 on Saturday. Paul Miller added 14 points with seven rebounds, and Kory Brown chipped in 12 points for the Bison (14-7, 4-3 Summit). Western Illinois (7-11, 0-7 Summit) was led by Tate Stensgaard and J.C. Fuller with 10 points apiece. Garret Covington grabbed 10 rebounds to go with nine points. A 7-0 spurt midway through the second half -- including back-to-back jumpers by Miller -- turned a three-point lead to 10 with 7:46 to go. Western Illinois cut the deficit to seven points on the ensuing two possessions, but the Leathernecks got no closer the rest of the way as the Bison made 8 of 10 free throw attempts down the stretch.
